00:00:05:190000.Speaker: Raj
00:00:05:190000.Dialogue: God, I love the smell of paintballs in the morning.

00:00:14:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:14:050000.Dialogue: We can't get to the ridge. The Chemistry Department has us completely cut off.

00:00:19:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:19:110000.Dialogue: The Pharmacology Department controls that, and they're all hopped up on experimental steroids.

00:00:26:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:26:130000.Dialogue: The time has come to acknowledge that we are paying the price for some of us failing to attend my Physics Department paintball strategy meeting.

00:00:33:030000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:33:030000.Dialogue: I told you my mom has spider veins. I had to take her to the laser clinic.

00:00:39:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:39:170000.Dialogue: And I told you I wanted to see a doctor's note.

00:00:44:030000.Speaker: Raj
00:00:44:030000.Dialogue: We need a plan. How about Operation Hammer of the Gods?

00:00:47:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:47:070000.Dialogue: Which one is Hammer of the Gods?

00:00:48:220000.Speaker: Raj
00:00:48:220000.Dialogue: We hide behind the dumpsters in the parking lot and ambush people when they come to pee.

00:00:54:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:54:040000.Dialogue: No go. The dumpsters are deep in Astronomy Department territory.

00:00:57:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:57:020000.Dialogue: That shouldn't be a problem. Venus is up during the day. They're probably just all staring at the sky.

00:01:01:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:01:230000.Dialogue: What we need now is a tactical retreat. Did you see the episode of Stargate where they found themselves on a planet with a culture based loosely on Earth's Athens and Sparta? Not important. Leonard, Raj and I are going to burst out the door and run away. Howard will cover us.

00:01:18:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:18:070000.Dialogue: Why don't I run away and you cover me?

00:01:20:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:20:040000.Dialogue: Because you chose your mother's veins over victory.

00:01:23:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:23:200000.Dialogue: On three. One, two, three, go!

00:01:29:060000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:29:060000.Dialogue: I had to take her! It's almost bathing suit weather!

00:01:38:190000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:38:190000.Dialogue: I surrender! Don't shoot! They went that way!

00:01:47:210000.Speaker: Leslie
00:01:47:210000.Dialogue: Where's the rest of your squad?

00:01:50:180000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:50:180000.Dialogue: They left me here to die. What about yours?

00:01:57:030000.Speaker: Leslie
00:01:57:030000.Dialogue: Don't be. It was friendly fire.

00:02:05:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:05:040000.Dialogue: Well, we're surrounded, so I guess there's nothing for us to do but wait to be captured or killed.

00:02:14:060000.Speaker: Leslie
00:02:14:060000.Dialogue: That's the worst part, the waiting.

00:02:17:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:17:100000.Dialogue: All the while knowing that there's a paint pellet out there with your name on it.

00:02:24:120000.Speaker: Leslie
00:02:24:120000.Dialogue: The big wet ball of death.

00:02:31:120000.Speaker: Leslie
00:02:31:120000.Dialogue: Kind of makes you feel more alive, doesn't it?

00:02:38:210000.Speaker: Leslie
00:02:38:210000.Dialogue: I say we make every moment count.

00:02:41:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:41:100000.Dialogue: I agree. How exactly do we do that?

00:02:49:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:49:170000.Dialogue: Why aren't you covering us?! We're getting slaughtered out here!

00:03:20:120000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:20:120000.Dialogue: Did you guys see the budget nemo that went out this morning?

00:03:24:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:24:150000.Dialogue: Unacceptable. It baffles me why they don't simply let some of you go so that there's money available for my research.

00:03:34:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:34:230000.Dialogue: Based on your academic record, any number of things, I imagine.

00:03:40:140000.Speaker: Leslie
00:03:40:140000.Dialogue: I got the approval for the rapid prototyper you wanted.

00:03:45:100000.Speaker: Leslie
00:03:45:100000.Dialogue: You scratch my back, I scratch yours.

00:03:53:060000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:53:060000.Dialogue: No big deal. They gave Leslie control of some unrestricted grant money.

00:03:58:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:58:030000.Dialogue: Yeah, okay, but what's with the back-scratching and the meow?

00:04:03:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:03:090000.Dialogue: I believe the back-scratching metaphor generally describes a quid pro quo situation where one party provides goods or services to the second party in compensation for a similar action.

00:04:22:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:22:170000.Dialogue: Despite what the name suggests, the civet cat is not a true cat.

00:04:33:150000.Speaker: Raj
00:04:33:150000.Dialogue: You know what I'm thinking? I'm thinking Howard wasn't making a back-scratching metaphor. I'm thinking there was some actual scratching involved.

00:04:46:060000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:46:060000.Dialogue: I didn't want to say anything 'cause I know you and Leslie have a little history.

00:04:51:180000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:51:180000.Dialogue: Great, I've been dying to say something.

00:04:59:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:59:040000.Dialogue: Is that why you didn't cover our escape and let us get cut down like animals?

00:05:07:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:07:050000.Dialogue: My good man, dereliction of duty in the face of the enemy is a court-martial offense.

00:05:12:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:05:12:200000.Dialogue: Court-martial, schmort-martial, Leslie Winkle is the fifth girl I've ever had sex with.

00:05:22:120000.Speaker: Raj
00:05:22:120000.Dialogue: Plus, you got a rapid prototyper. That's an expensive piece of equipment.

00:05:26:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:26:100000.Dialogue: And the rest of us have had our budgets cut to the bone.

00:05:29:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:05:29:140000.Dialogue: One way to look at this is that I'm getting new equipment, and you're not, and that's unfair. But a better way to look at this is that I'm getting sex and you're not, and that's delightful.

00:15:00:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:00:220000.Dialogue: Thank you. It helps when I get to practice with a real woman.

00:15:07:110000.Speaker: Leslie
00:15:07:110000.Dialogue: Listen. Saturday my sister's getting married. I want you to come with me. It's black tie.

00:15:13:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:13:100000.Dialogue: Yeah, gee... I'd really rather not.

00:15:18:210000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:18:210000.Dialogue: When I go to weddings, it's to scam on chunky bridesmaids. I don't know what I would do with a date.

00:15:32:120000.Speaker: Leslie
00:15:32:120000.Dialogue: I'm really sorry about that Geneva trip.

00:15:47:180000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:47:180000.Dialogue: Well, hold on. Are you... saying if I don't go to the wedding, I can't go to Geneva?

00:15:53:130000.Speaker: Leslie
00:15:53:130000.Dialogue: Actually, I'm trying not to say it.

00:15:56:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:56:100000.Dialogue: Okay, I'm sorry, but that makes me a little uncomfortable.

00:16:05:070000.Speaker: Leslie
00:16:05:070000.Dialogue: If I weren't controlling you with new equipment and research trips, - then I'd be uncomfortable.

00:16:10:140000.Speaker: Leslie
00:16:10:140000.Dialogue: 'Cause we'd be in a real relationship with feelings and all that crap.

00:16:16:230000.Speaker: Howard
00:16:16:230000.Dialogue: So, bottom line, I'm just a... bought-and-paid-for sex toy.

00:16:26:140000.Speaker: Leslie
00:16:26:140000.Dialogue: No, not at all. You're also arm candy. So? What do you think?

00:16:34:190000.Speaker: Howard
00:16:34:190000.Dialogue: Hey, Ma, you got to rent me a tux!

00:16:38:150000.Speaker: Howard’s Mother
00:16:38:150000.Dialogue: Right now? What kind of sex are you having up there?

00:16:57:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:57:170000.Dialogue: Where else am I supposed to crouch?

00:17:06:150000.Speaker: Penny
00:17:06:150000.Dialogue: Here you go. Fresh from the cleaners, good as new.

00:17:08:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:08:210000.Dialogue: Really? Great. Sheldon, look. Good as new.

00:17:11:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:11:190000.Dialogue: From that key maker, I highly doubt it.

00:17:15:050000.Speaker: Penny
00:17:15:050000.Dialogue: Come on, Sheldon. Just give it a try.

00:17:23:210000.Speaker: Penny
00:17:23:210000.Dialogue: There, nice and comfy cozy. Zero, zero, zero.

00:18:02:050000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:02:050000.Dialogue: What do you mean, nope? What's wrong with it?

00:18:04:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:04:110000.Dialogue: Nothing, it's what's wrong with him.

00:18:09:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:09:150000.Dialogue: Penny, I think I know what to do. Sheldon, I have some bad news.

00:18:17:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:17:110000.Dialogue: I'm afraid so. You know the cashew chicken I get you Monday nights?

00:18:24:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:24:080000.Dialogue: Szechuan Palace closed two years ago.

00:18:29:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:29:150000.Dialogue: What? Where did my cashew chicken come from?

00:18:44:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:44:060000.Dialogue: No, this isn't right. Our food always comes in Szechuan Palace containers.

00:18:49:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:49:140000.Dialogue: Yeah, well, before they went out of business, I bought 4,000 containers.

00:18:55:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:55:210000.Dialogue: I keep them in the trunk of my car.

00:19:05:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:05:170000.Dialogue: I thought that might take his mind off the cushion.

00:19:08:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:08:180000.Dialogue: What's real? What isn't? How can I know?

00:19:13:130000.Speaker: Penny
00:19:13:130000.Dialogue: - You did make that up, right? - Oh, God, I wish I had.

00:19:20:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:20:130000.Dialogue: I still don't like this cushion.

00:19:25:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:25:160000.Dialogue: Okay, first of all, Penny, thank you for coming.

00:19:30:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:30:210000.Dialogue: Penny is an amazing shot. We have a real chance to win this week.

00:19:47:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:47:190000.Dialogue: - Just one thing before we start.

00:19:58:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:58:130000.Dialogue: Sheldon, Penny was our only hope.

00:20:01:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:01:030000.Dialogue: I'm sorry. But revenge is a dish best served cold.

00:20:11:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:11:180000.Dialogue: She can't shoot me. She's dead.

00:20:21:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:21:220000.Dialogue: Well, if we're going to descend into anarchy...
